that the next time step

00:48:11.410 --> 00:48:12.344
it should be higher.

00:48:12.344 --> 00:48:13.760
But if you think
about it, it also

00:48:13.760 --> 00:48:16.590
predicts that the previous
time step should be higher.

00:48:16.590 --> 00:48:18.890
So the entropic
arrow is sometimes

00:48:18.890 --> 00:48:22.300
called a bi-directional
arrow that doesn't explain

00:48:22.300 --> 00:48:23.670
the arrow of time by itself.

00:48:23.670 --> 00:48:27.020
It needs to be coupled with
an assumption about a lower

00:48:27.020 --> 00:48:28.200
initial state.

